tatistical area classifications a task it has done every decade since the 1950 Census OMB establishes and maintains the definitions of these areas solely for statistical purposes This classification is intended to provide nationally consistent definitions for collecting tabulating and publishing federal statistics for a set of geographic areas Within the Bureau of Labor Statistics information on the publication plans of employment and unemployment programs that produce data for statistical areas is shown below New definitions http www whitehouse gov omb bulletins b03 04 html OMB Bulletin 03 04 Comparison of geographic coverage between the 2000 and 1990 definitions United States Maps of 2000 Metropolitan Micropolitan Areas vs 1990 Metropolitan Areas http www bls gov lau maps uscmpr htm HTML http www bls gov lau maps uscmpr pdf PDF 550K New England Maps of 2000 Metropolitan Micropolitan NECTAs vs 1990 Metropolitan Areas http www bls gov lau maps necmpr htm HTML http www bls gov lau maps necmpr pdf PDF 126K Census Bureau links to information about Metropolitan Areas http www census gov population www estimates aboutmetro html Background http www census gov population www estimates metrodef html Current Definitions and FIPS Codes http www census gov population www estimates pastmetro html Historical Metropolitan Area Definitions Federal Register Notice Final Standards http www census gov population www estimates 00 32997 pdf PDF 295K http www census gov geo www ua ua 2k html Census 2000 Urban and Rural Classification BLS links to data on Metropolitan Areas lamet implement3 htm Metropolitan Area Implementation Plans for the Fed State Programs http www bls gov bls geography htm BLS programs by geography BLS Publications of Metropolitan Area data http www bls gov schedule archives metro nr htm Metropolitan Area Employment and Unemployment http www bls gov oes 2001 oessrcma htm Metropolitan Area Occupational Employment and Wage Estimates http www bls gov opub gp laugp htm G